body.description: With the Samsung Galaxy A10e, you get exactly what you need with the performance and reliability from a brand you can trust. Do more with a long-lasting battery, keep all of your stuff with a 32GB built-in memory, and experience it on a 5.83" edge-to-edge Infinity Display. Finally, the phone you need to keep connected with friends and family—and at just the right price. With a long-lasting battery, the Galaxy A10e gives you more time to post, talk, text and share with friends and family. Keep more with 32GB of built-in memory, so you can keep all of your photos, shows, movies and apps, without having to delete to make room. If you need more storage, expand your memory up to 512GB with a microSD card and store up to 100,000 photos. Enjoy a bold, bright viewing experience on a 5.83" screen. With an Infinity Display that goes edge-to-edge, you can see more story before you scroll. The Galaxy A10e lets you make everyday moments special. Take crisp, clear photos with an 8MP rear camera and perfect selfies with the kids on a 5MP front camera.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best phone ever - one MINOR problem
reviews.reviewText: Great phone and perfect size. Tried to transfer my Straight Talk to it from one just like it - not compatible. Unlocked?? I thought so. But it doesn't work. I wish there was a way to contact the seller. I'll try to unlock it over the internet and see if it works for me. In any event, the A10E is the best IMHO. The more modern phones are like little suitcases and you can hardly take them anywhere. The A10E fits into any pocket and basically disappears there. UPDATE - I'm not paying to unlock the phone. Already bought a SIM card that won't activate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Got a bad phone
reviews.reviewText: The Phone was in a factory package but upon opening it would not charge after many attempts it finally began to charge. So I began setting up the phone . Initially I was on WiFi so setup proceeded as expected, then I switched off WiFi and discovered that the phone was locked from att Sim use. I noticed that the phone was a tracphone so I contacted tfunlock and after 24 Hrs was able to unlock. But the phone would not work on data plan so I researched how to setup the APN settings to look like my other phone but they were greyed out. There were four options before a factory reset and on the forth I was able to force APN settings that worked with att but it was still using the VMNO setting that are forced on tracfone which delivers way weaker signal than my other phones about 20 dbm's which is significant signal loss. So thought ID contact the manufacturer. I connected the charger and attempted to continue setting up the next day but the phone has not recharged since and I have tried two different chargers and 3 different cords all of which work on my other phones.

reviews.reviewText: Por el precio no me quejo mucho, vino únicamente con un cargador original. El celular es bueno para un uso muy tranquilo, ya que intentar jugar un juego o hacer algo que no sea usar redes sociales, hace que se vuelva muy lento, se atore e incluso llegue a crashear, es bueno para una emergencia pero no para un celular que se necesite para mucho uso constante. La pila le dura aproximadamente 13 horas considerando un uso moderado.
